Looking for some super easy ideas for your Game  Day spread? Look no further!🙌 Here are three delicious #LowCarb recipes that would be perfect for the Big Game! 🍕🌭😋
...
📝 Notes by Lori , @lori.monigold , the Amazing Chef 👩‍🍳:

1.🍕Crispy Pizza Pockets:

To make these grab your flatbreads, shredded cheese, some mini pepperonis( or regular pepperonis diced up small), and some marinara for dunking. Place flatbread on parchment and cover with a thin ayer of cheese. Microwave 30 seconds or until cheese is melty. Cut into four strips. Add pepperoni and cheese and fold into overlapping triangles until you reach the end (see video). Heat some oil in a skillet over medium heat and fry until golden and crisp, about 2-3 minutes per side. Place on paper towel lined plate to drain off any excess oil and serve with your favorite marinara or ranch dipping sauce.

2.🌭Cheesy Crunch Dogs:

To make these heat some oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add hot dogs and cook 4-6 minutes(Save oil for frying again). Remove to towel lined plate and prepare your flatbreads by cutting one sheet into four equal sections. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on the edge furthest from you. Place one hot dog on each section of bread closest to you. Sprinkle cheese over bread between hot dog and cream cheese. Roll tightly and crisp in oiled pan over medium heat 3-4 minutes per side. These could also be done in an air fryer at 350 degrees for 6-8 minutes flipping half way through.

3.🔺Crispy Homemade Chips:

Cut your flatbreads into fourths and then into triangles. Heat oil over medium heat in a pot. Fry chips until golden and crisp watching closely as this only takes a few seconds. Enjoy with dips of choice like; guacamole, salsa, or queso.

📝Pro tip: Work with 1-2 flatbreads at a time keeping the rest sealed in bag to prevent drying of bread.
.

Happy #nationalpickleday !!..🤩
Here’s @annies_keto incredibly delicious Fried Pickle Chip recipe to celebrate this delicious day!!!🙌😍.
For all of the pickle lovers out there, this amazing recipe will become a staple in your #lowcarblife !!🥒🤯
...
Recipe and video credit: @Annies_keto. Thank you so much for the amazing recipe!🙏💕😊
...
Ingredients:
1/2 cup of full pickle chips
1 egg
3 sheets of @cutdacarb flatbreads
1 tbs pickle juice
1 tbs Old Bay seasoning
1 tbs garlic powder 
1 tsp pepper
...
Instructions: 
1. Dry out flatbreads in the oven at 200 degrees for 20 minutes.
2.  Break flatbreads into bread crumbs (by hand or blender). 3. Beat egg, pickle juice, seasonings and hot sauce (optional) to create egg wash. 
4. Dip each pickle into egg wash and then into bread crumbs (patting the crumbs in for a thick layer). 5. Shallow fry in your oil of choice. 
6. Fry each side until golden brown. 
7. Once removed from oil, sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning (optional). 8. Enjoy! .
.

Ever wondered how you can make the perfect shells for your Cut Da Carb Cannolis without a Cannoli Shell maker?!.. 🤔. Wonder no more!..Here, Allie is showing you all you need to know!.. 👏🙏😍.
✅About 2 Net Carbs for Each Cannoli !…😳
.
.
 #Repost @eat.keto.af .. Thank you Allie for the amazing creation and showing us this perfect and yet simple method for making these crunchy shells!..🙏😍💕 ・・・
The air fryer comes through! Such a great no-mess, no-fuss option for frying things. I thought @cutdacarb would work as cannoli shells and it did! So good! There is a little technique involved but overall it’s easy and comes together simply! A great snack or dessert for any time of day

Keto cannoli using @cutdacarb

INGREDIENTS
4 cannolis
// 1 sheet @cutdacarb flatbreads
// 1 egg, lightly beaten
// oil spray
// 15 oz ricotta
// 3 tbsp zero calorie sweetener + more for dusting
// 10 drops sweetener
// 3 squares sugar free 70% dark chocolate
// 24 sugar free semi-sweet chocolate chips

METHOD
1. Make 4 tinfoil molds. Watch my highlight for my homemade foil mold method!
2. Cut out 4 circles from the @cutdacarb flatbreads. I used the top of the 15 oz ricotta container for a stencil and it fit 4 rounds perfectly
3. Lightly spray the molds with some oil wrap each with a mold and seal with egg. Also brush all over with egg. Set seam side down to hold the seal
4. Spritz fryer and shells with oil and air fry 2 at a time at 400*F for 2 mins. Don’t overcook! Should be slightly darker than the plain flatbreads but not too golden
5. Let cool for 1 minute then remove tinfoil (my method in my IGTV video) and let fully cool
6. While shells are cooling, mix together ricotta, confectioners sweetener, and sweet drops
7. Melt chocolate in microwave, dip shell ends in, then set them in fridge for 5 mins on chopsticks
8. Put filling in piping bag or plastic bag with corner cut off. Piped into shell and add chocolate chops and a dusting of confectioners
9. Enjoy!

Oh how we all love crab Rangoons!..A perfect creamy and crispy bite!..👌😋
...

crab rangoons using @cutdacarb for the first time!! I have to say I’m officially obsessed with cut-da-carb and I can’t wait to make more things with it! What is your favorite thing to make with it?? It crisped up perfectly and I was able to seal the edges quite easily using water - so so impressed!! As for the filling - it was delicious but not exactly what I was looking for when it comes to crab rangoons. I’d like to try using real crab meat and play with adding a sweetener next time. I’ll keep you posted when I come up with the perfect filling! After sealing the filling in the “shells” I brushed them with avocado oil and then cooked them in the air fryer at 380 for 5 minutes. It was the perfect amount of time! I just need to find the right filling now...

Many of you have been asking us to share @annies_keto incredibly delicious Fried Pickle Chip recipe and so here it is!!🙌😍 For all of the pickle lovers out there, this amazing recipe will become a staple in your #lowcarblife!!🥒🤯
...
Recipe and video credit: @Annies_keto. Thank you so much for the amazing recipe!🙏💕😊
...
Ingredients:
1/2 cup of full pickle chips
1 egg
3 sheets of @cutdacarb flatbreads
1 tbs pickle juice
1 tbs Old Bay seasoning
1 tbs garlic powder 
1 tsp pepper
...
Instructions: 
1. Dry out flatbreads in the oven at 200 degrees for 20 minutes.
2.  Break flatbreads into bread crumbs (by hand or blender). 3. Beat egg, pickle juice, seasonings and hot sauce (optional) to create egg wash. 
4. Dip each pickle into egg wash and then into bread crumbs (patting the crumbs in for a thick layer). 5. Shallow fry in your oil of choice. 
6. Fry each side until golden brown. 
7. Once removed from oil, sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning (optional). 8. Enjoy! .
.
.
.

Ya'll know how delicious Cut Da Carb Chips are  and we have Joey, from @lowcarb_joey here,  to show 3 easy ways of making these Homemade and all natural chips 😍🤤
✅One Flatbread can be cut into 5 sections and cut into 30 chips for ONLY 9 Grams of Net carbs! 😳❗️.... Have Your Chips and Eat them too😋
.
.
______
Instructions: ...
✅Method 1: FRYING
Bring a small pan of oil to high heat but not smoking point. Fry in small batches to get color consistency. They fry for less than 10 seconds. Drain excess oil on paper towel.
...
✅Method 2: BAKING
Arrange Chips on a piece of parchment paper or foil and then place in a baking pan. Coat with cooking oil and then season to your liking and bake at 350 for 5 to Maximum 10 minutes depending on your oven setting and power. *Keep an eye out as they color fast *
...
✅Method 3:MICROWAVE
Arrange Chips on a piece of parchment paper or paper towel, coat with cooking oil and then season to your liking and Microwave for 1 to Maximum 2 minutes depending on your microwave setting and power. *Keep an eye out as they color fast*

💃🍔Fiesta Crunch Wrap Double CheeseBurger, #LowCarbStyle !!.
This is what Burger Dreams are made of!!😋😋
@Lori.monigold Aced this one!👏👏.
…
📝Notes by Lori:
This Tex-Mex spin on an American favorite is a great way to change up burger night y’all!!! If you haven’t taken a Cut Da Carb flatbread and crunch wrapped your burger yet then might I suggest you do so. Its the perfect wrapping to the gift that is the burger… Crispy, crunchy, and absolutely delicious you will never want to bun your burger again 🤗

⭐️To make these you will need:

2 Cut Da Carb Flatbreads (for 2 Burgers)
1lb ground beef, divided by 4 and made into thin burger patties
2 bell peppers, sliced thin
1 onion, sliced thin
1 avocado, mashed
Shredded cheese
Spray oil
Salt and Pepper

🔥Directions:

1. Prepare your veggies and cook them in an oiled skillet over medium-high heat until caramelized. Set aside.
2. In the same preheated skillet cook your burgers to your desired level of doneness. Season to taste. 
3. Grab a Cut Da Carb flatbread and place some of the mashed avocado in the center.Season with salt and pepper.
4. Add on some of the peppers and onions, one burger patty, shredded cheese,and  then another burger patty. 
5. Fold the flatbread around the burger creasing the edges as you go. Place seam side down onto baking sheet. 
6. Air Fry or bake at 325 for 10 minutes(longer if baking). 
7. Slice in half and enjoy!!!

⭐️Tip: To make your flatbread more pliable for folding lay one flatbread on some damp paper towels. Roll the bread up with the towel and microwave 15 seconds. This will steam the bread and make it very flexible for folding and prevent any cracking or tearing.

✅Only 9g Net Carbs and 80 Calories for this Footlong Crust!🤩.

📝Notes by  Fojan, @_dashofhappiness_ :
KETO SUNDRIED TOMATO PESTO  BREAKFAST PIZZA W/ @cutdacarb 🌟 ohmygosh this turned out SO delicious! Soft scrambled cheesy eggs, red onions, sun-dried pesto, and fresh basil made this breakfast a home run for us this morning!

This is my 2nd entry for the #cutdacarbpizza contest and it is always a hit when i make it! 
.
.
.
@kristysketolifestyle  @cutdacarb 
🤍
TO MAKE:
Soft scramble your eggs & add about 1/4 cup cheese and mix around. Top with paprika, salt & pepper. Spread about 1 to 1 1/2 tbs mezzetta sun-dried tomato pesto on your @cutdacarb - add the eggs. Top with pepperoni bits, bacon or sausage (i used turkey pepperoni and it complimented the sun-dried pesto PERFECTLY) - top with more cheese (I used colby jack), red onions thinly sliced. Bake in oven for 6-7minutes at 325°F - just enough to get it crispy..watch to prevent burning. Remove and top with fresh basil. ENJOY 🥰

📝Notes by Duri:
🚨Low Carb And Low Calorie Recipe Alert 🚨
@cutdacarb flatbreads are an amazing substitute for #highcarb pizza crust. This recipe can be found on the back of the package. It’s my go to #healthysnack when I’m in a rush. 

1. Preheat oven to 375°
2. Brush cut da carb with oil or butter
3. Brush flatbread with very light pizza sauce
4. Add toppings of your choice. I added mushrooms and jalapeños.
5. Add cheese and more sauce on top as desired
6. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes

I sprinkled my pizza with crushed Chilli flakes and oregano. Then let it rest for a couple of minutes and enjoy this flatbread pizza with a lot less guilt 🍕🤗

📝Notes by: @thelowcarbcontessa :
 “BBQ Pulled Pork Pizza” This my friends is how you turn ordinary into EXTRAORDINARY! 
This weekend I took a big ol’ pork butt/shoulder roast, rubbed it down with some @flavorgod Honey BBQ Seasoning, and then threw that baby in the slow cooker! It was DELICIOUS! But, here's my problem, I had some leftover pork roast, and my hubs doesn't really love leftovers! What's a girl to do? Well, ya change it into something completely different🙌!

Here's what I did...
I used 2 @cutdacarb flatbread cut into circles and glued them together with a bit of beaten egg whites. I then brushed each side of my crust with a bit of melted butter that I seasoned with @flavorgodseasoning Garlic Lovers, and popped it in the oven at 375° F for 6 minutes, turning halfway through.

Once out of the oven, I allowed my crust to cool just a bit. I then brushed on some sugar-free BBQ sauce, and added my toppings! For this pizza, I used smoked gouda, my seasoned pulled pork, sliced red onions, and jalapenos. For my husband’s pizza (not shown) I cut some leftover corn off the cob and added that as well. Then I returned the pizza to the oven for approximately 6-8 minutes to allow the cheese to melt, and the veggies to soften a bit. 

NOTES: I like my veggies with a bit of crunch. If you like softer veggies on your pizza, you may want to saute them a bit first before adding them to your pizza. This pizza would be equally delicious with Chicken or Beef!!!
Lastly, I topped my pizza with additional bbq sauce, and fresh chopped cilantro, it was DELISH! So delish that I'm making it my 2nd entry of the #cutdacarbpizza contest with @cutdacarb & @kristysketolifestyle!

🔥Hot Ham & Swiss Pinwheels, #lowcarbstyle !.
…
We love all creations by Christii, @on_westhoff_ranch and these yummy looking Pinwheels, are no exception!!👏😋.
✅Less than 2g Net Carbs per slider!🤩
…
📝Notes by Christii:
Hot Ham & Swiss Pinwheels
(2 ways)
I remember having these as sliders back in the day. 
It was a recipe that everyone was making from Pinterest and Facebook. Does anyone remember these? 
They were delicious, and so are these!
✅Ingredients:
2 sheets @cutdacarb 
18 slices Deli ham
18 slices Swiss
✅Sauce Version #1:
1 stick butter, melted
1 1/2TB Dijon
1TB Minced dried onion, 
or 1 1/2TB fresh minced onion
1tsp Worcestershire sauce
1TB poppyseeds
Mix all together in a small bowl.

-OR-

✅Sauce Version #2
1 stick butter
1TB Dijon 
1TB Worcestershire sauce
2TB Brown sugar substitute
1TB Poppyseeds
Whisk all together in a small saucepan till it comes to a simmer. Remove from heat.
✅Assembly:
Layer each @cutdacarb sheet with 9 slices of ham or more to cover. Layer each with 9 slices of Swiss or more to cover. Roll up from the short side. Slice each roll into 8 pinwheels.
Assemble in a single layer into a greased cast iron skillet, baking dish, or in muffin tins.
Pour one of the sauce versions on top.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350 degree oven for 25 minutes. Then run under broiler for 2 minutes. Just until golden & bubbly.
*Ketofied recipe from Pinterest by Kevin&Amanda.

📝Notes by Kristy:
I decided on something a little different for #tacotuesday last week and it was a hit with my family!  I'll be making this dish often. 😋🙌🌮
I use @cutdacarb for my "noodles" and they turned out awesome!.

✅RECIPE:
1. Make 1 lb of taco meat however you like to. I'll share below how I make mine. 
2. In a bowl, mix 1 can of rotel, 1/2 cup of Queso Blanco (I buy this at Dollar General) and 1/2 cup of sour cream.
3. Stir in the taco meat. 
4. In a greased 9x13 baking dish, layer:
•flatbread 
•1/3 of the taco mixture 
•shredded cheese (I used Monterey Jack & Colby)
5. Repeat 2 more times ending with shredded cheese on top. 
6. Bake at 375° for 15-20 minutes. 
.
TACO MEAT: 
1. Brown 1 lbs of ground beef with 1/2 of a chopped onion.
2. Stir in 2 tbsp of my homemade taco seasoning along with 1/4 cup of water.
